---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Speed Limits Worldwide: mph vs km/h by Country" description="Compare speed limits around the world in mph and km/h. See which countries use which system and the fastest legal highways on Earth." keywords="speed limits worldwide, mph vs km/h, speed limit by country, road speed conversion, highway speed limits, fastest speed limits, autobahn speed">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Speed</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Speed Limits Worldwide: mph vs km/h by Country</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 24, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Driving abroad means understanding different speed limit systems. Only a handful of countries use miles per hour — the rest of the world measures speed in kilometres per hour. Here is your guide to speed limits globally.</p>

      <h2>The Conversion</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">1 mph = 1.609 km/h | 1 km/h = 0.621 mph</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Quick trick: mph × 1.6 = km/h (or km/h ÷ 1.6 = mph)</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Countries That Use mph</h2>
      <p>Only these nations measure road speed in miles per hour:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>United States</li>
        <li>United Kingdom</li>
        <li>Myanmar</li>
        <li>Liberia</li>
        <li>Some Caribbean islands (Bahamas, Cayman Islands)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Every other country uses km/h on road signs.</p>

      <h2>Highway Speed Limits Compared</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Germany (Autobahn):</strong> No limit on many sections (advisory 130 km/h / 81 mph)</li>
        <li><strong>Poland:</strong> 140 km/h (87 mph)</li>
        <li><strong>France:</strong> 130 km/h (81 mph)</li>
        <li><strong>Italy:</strong> 130 km/h (81 mph)</li>
        <li><strong>UK:</strong> 70 mph (113 km/h)</li>
        <li><strong>USA (Texas toll road):</strong> 85 mph (137 km/h) — highest posted limit in the US</li>
        <li><strong>USA (most interstates):</strong> 65-75 mph (105-121 km/h)</li>
        <li><strong>Australia (Northern Territory):</strong> 130 km/h (81 mph)</li>
        <li><strong>UAE:</strong> 140 km/h (87 mph) on some roads</li>
        <li><strong>Japan:</strong> 100-120 km/h (62-75 mph)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Common Speed Limit Conversions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>30 mph = 48 km/h (residential streets)</li>
        <li>50 km/h = 31 mph (city speed in metric countries)</li>
        <li>60 mph = 97 km/h</li>
        <li>70 mph = 113 km/h</li>
        <li>100 km/h = 62 mph</li>
        <li>120 km/h = 75 mph</li>
        <li>130 km/h = 81 mph</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tips for Driving in a Different System</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Most rental cars</strong> show both mph and km/h on the speedometer</li>
        <li><strong>GPS navigation</strong> can display speed in either unit — switch to match local signs</li>
        <li><strong>Remember key anchors:</strong> 50 km/h in town, 100-130 km/h on highways</li>
        <li><strong>Speed cameras abroad</strong> have zero tolerance for "I didn't understand the sign" excuses</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/speed" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Speed Converter →</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
